description.narrative:
PSCM-PS is a network organization with the main objective of advocating for the improvement of social security services such as pension schemes. It was established in 2008 as a network organization that strives for transparency, accessibility and qualityof socialprotection services for orphans, elderly people, women and handicapped persons. Its main achievement is that it exercised advocacy to convince the Government to increase the budget for social protection. This partner has also engaged with the government in order to implement the national programme on basic social subsidy which is a programme destined to ensure secure basic needs for the vulnerable groups including older people, the disabled and people living with HIV and AIDS. Over the last years this partner has implemented the community independent monitoring system.

With the Innovative funds PSCM-PS will acquire a Complaints Management System in the Basic Social Subsidy Program (PSSB) implemented by INAS through a Digital Platform using the Web Technology Platform with an Android application under the Independent Community Monitoring Program and is hoping to address the issue of social inclusion of marginalized and vulnerable groups, as well as the non-discrimination of these groups, and these themes are of great importance for AGIR program. the main outcomes are:
1. Reduced costs and time of complaints from beneficiaries to service providers;
2. Beneficiaries are satisfied with the timely feedback of their complaints and complaints as aresult of greater case management efficiency;
3. Increasednumber of complaints and complaints as a result of using a reliable, stealthy instrument to convey user concerns.
